<TITLE> We want a united BNP under Khaleda: Hafiz </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 10 (bdnews24.com)- BNP acting secretary general Hafizuddin Ahmed expressed satisfaction Thursday after the High Court dismissed a writ petition by former prime minister Khaleda Zia challenging the Election Commission's invitation to his 'reformist' faction for electoral reform talks. In an instant reaction, he told bdnews24.com Thursday: "We have got justice. BNP will be run by Khaleda Zia." "We want to sit for dialogue with the Election Commission with a united BNP delegation after consulting with senior leaders including Khandaker Delwar Hossain and ASM Hannan Shah," the acting secretary general said. Assuring party leaders and workers at home and abroad, Hafizuddin said: "All remain united under the leadership of Khaleda Zia; she is also my leader." "A united BNP will participate in the next election." Hafizuddin is expected to give a more complete statement at a press briefing at his Banani home Thursday afternoon. bdnew
